    @startuml
actor Student
participant "Frontend" as Frontend
participant "Backend" as Backend
participant "Database" as Database
participant "FSRS Engine" as FSRS

== 1. Session Start ==
Student -> Frontend : Click "Start Practice"
Frontend -> Backend : GET /api/topics/due
Backend -> Database : SELECT * FROM TopicMastery WHERE next_review <= TODAY
Database --> Backend : [Logic (Stability: 0.8), Sets (Stability: 4.5)]
note right: "Logic" is weak. "Sets" is strong.

== 2. Adaptive Scaffolding (The AI Logic) ==
Backend -> Backend : Calculate Question Tier
note right
  If Stability < 1.0 -> Tier 1 (Basics)
  If Stability > 3.0 -> Tier 3 (Advanced)
end note
Backend -> Database : SELECT * FROM Question \nWHERE topic="Logic" AND tier=1 \nORDER BY RANDOM() LIMIT 1
Database --> Backend : Returns Tier 1 Question

== 3. Active Practice ==
Backend --> Frontend : Display Question
Student -> Frontend : Submit Answer (Correct)
Frontend -> Backend : POST /api/reviews

== 4. Update FSRS & Gamification ==
Backend -> FSRS : fsrs.schedule(rating=Good)
FSRS --> Backend : New Stability (2.1)
Backend -> Backend : Calculate XP (Base * Difficulty)
Backend -> Database : Update TopicMastery & Save Review
Backend --> Frontend : {correct: true, xp: +100, next_review: "3 days"}
@enduml